Two points to help you solve the problem:
-----------------------------------------

1. Use [getNextDataCell(direction)][1]
It returns you the last contents containing cell of a continuous data range. 

**Sample:**

``` lang:js
var lastCell=sessionSheet.getRange(&quot;C14&quot;).getNextDataCell(SpreadsheetApp.Direction.DOWN);
Logger.log(lastCell.getA1Notation());
```

&gt; If the the value of `lastCell` is e.g. `C19` you know that your first
&gt; data range goes from row 14 to row 19.

2. Implement a counter variable within your formula statement.

**Sample:**
```lang:js
